        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2013-01-10 13:32:57.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "yong.fan@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2013-01-10 19:43:41.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-2638 ldiskfs: update dotdot entry for rename",
        "message": "LU-2638 ldiskfs: update dotdot entry for rename\n\nOn master, when rename a directory, its old dotdot entry will\nbe removed firstly, then insert the new dotdot entry, and try\nto append FID-in-dirent. But the space for dotdot entry maybe\nnot enough to hold the new dotdot with FID-in-dirent, such as\nthe MDT device restored from file-level backup, or the device\nis upgraded from 1.8. If we do not move data in the directory\nblock, the FID-in-dirent will overwrite the dx_root and cause\nthe directory crashed. Currently, we do not want to introduce\ncomplex logic to handle directory data moving, instead, under\nsuch case, ignore the FID-in-dirent for the new dotdot entry,\nand just insert the new dotdot entry.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: Id38f5136fb2bc607344c37ca10a32e63ab427e3d\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
